            <title>[HBASE-5370] Allow HBase shell to set HTableDescriptor values</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5370</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently it does not seem to be possible to set value on a table&apos;s HTableDescriptor (either on creation or afterwards).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The syntax I have in mind is something like:&lt;br/&gt;
create &lt;/p&gt;
{NAME=&amp;gt;&apos;table&apos;, &apos;somekey&apos;=&amp;gt;&apos;somevalue&apos;}
&lt;p&gt;, &apos;column&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In analogy to how we allow a column to either a string (&apos;column&apos;) or an association &lt;/p&gt;
{NAME=&amp;gt;&apos;column&apos;, ...}

&lt;p&gt;alter would be changed to allow setting arbitrary values.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
